    "description": "Modbus is a client-server industrial communication protocol used for reading and writing data in industrial automation systems. It defines a simple request-response message structure. The core application protocol uses function codes to operate on coils, discrete inputs, holding registers, and input registers. Modbus RTU and Modbus ASCII are serial transport encodings, while Modbus TCP encapsulates Modbus Application Protocol data in TCP/IP with a MBAP header.",
